wdi2-NV.MNF.FBTO.ZS.UN.def: Value added in manufacturing is the sum of gross output less the value of intermediate inputs used in production for industries classified in ISIC major division D. Food, beverages, and tobacco correspond to ISIC divisions 15 and 16.
wdi2-NV.MNF.FBTO.ZS.UN.name: Food, beverages and tobacco
wdi2-NV.MNF.FBTO.ZS.UN.source: United Nations Industrial Development Organization, International Yearbook of Industrial Statistics.
